abstract: The computer phishing attack that Google says originated in China aimed at officials who worked in areas not limited to those of particular interest to the Chinese government.
snippet: The computer phishing attack that Google says originated in China aimed at officials who worked in areas not limited to those of particular interest to the Chinese government.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The computer phishing attack that Google says originated in China was directed, somewhat indiscriminately, at an unknown number of White House staff officials, setting off the Federal Bureau of Investigation inquiry that began this week, according to several administration officials.

headline.main: Hacking of White House E-Mail Affected Diverse Departments
headline.print_headline: Hacking of White House Gmail Affected Diverse Departments

byline.original: By David E. Sanger and Verne G. Kopytoff
